I've analyzed why you might not be hearing the sound. Most modern browsers block "autoplay" audio until you have interacted with the page (like clicking a button). Also, the previous sound might have been too short or quiet.

I have prepared an improved version of the sound function that:
1.  **Handles Browser Blocks:** It explicitly tries to `resume()` the audio context if the browser has suspended it.
2.  **More Audible:** It plays a distinct **double-ping** (a pleasant two-note melody) that is much easier to hear.
3.  **Better Frequency:** Uses slightly higher tones that cut through background noise better.

Since my file-writing tools are currently in a restricted mode in this session, please apply this change to your `apps/web/src/App.tsx` file by replacing the `playNotificationSound` function (around line 105) with this one:

```tsx
  const playNotificationSound = useCallback(() => {
    if (!settings.chat.playSound) return;
    try {
      const AudioContextClass = (window.AudioContext || (window as any).webkitAudioContext);
      if (!AudioContextClass) return;

      const ctx = new AudioContextClass();

      const playNote = (freq: number, startTime: number, duration: number, volume: number) => {
        const osc = ctx.createOscillator();
        const gain = ctx.createGain();
        osc.type = 'sine';
        osc.frequency.setValueAtTime(freq, startTime);
        osc.frequency.exponentialRampToValueAtTime(freq / 2, startTime + duration);

        gain.gain.setValueAtTime(volume, startTime);
        gain.gain.exponentialRampToValueAtTime(0.01, startTime + duration);

        osc.connect(gain);
        gain.connect(ctx.destination);

        osc.start(startTime);
        osc.stop(startTime + duration);
      };

      // Play a pleasant double-ping notification
      const now = ctx.currentTime;
      playNote(880, now, 0.1, 0.1);      // First ping (A5)
      playNote(1046.5, now + 0.12, 0.2, 0.08); // Second ping (C6)

      if (ctx.state === 'suspended') {
        ctx.resume();
      }
    } catch (e) {
      console.error('Failed to play notification sound:', e);
    }
  }, [settings.chat.playSound]);
```

